overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their recently
  implemented sleep questionnaire application. The primary intent was to
  validate that the current implementation, including its database and API
  endpoints, fully satisfies the acceptance criteria outlined in a detailed
  project specification. The application is designed as an interactive,
  psychometrically validated questionnaire that provides users with a narrative
  report, linking to educational resources and clinicians. It operates on a
  freemium model, collecting minimal de-identified demographic data. The review
  process involved examining numerous code files across the application's
  frontend and backend, covering questionnaire logic, data capture, report
  generation (including PDF and CSV export), and administrative functionalities
  like user authentication and a dashboard. The goal was to identify any missing
  features or discrepancies against the specified requirements for sleep health
  optimization and sleep disorder screening.
